   _______________________________________________________________________

                       System Requirements

   Sedna runs on the following platforms:
   - Windows 2000/XP
   - Linux x86 kernel version 2.4 or higher
   - Mac OS X (PPC/Intel)
   - FreeBSD 
   - Solaris (x86)


   _______________________________________________________________________

            Installing Sedna from Source Code 

   See file INSTALL supplied with the source code package.


   _______________________________________________________________________

            Installing Sedna from Precompiled Binaries

Windows platform:

   Sedna is distributed as a single ".tar.gz" archive. 

   The installation process consists of the following steps:

   1) Unzip archive to any directory (for example "c:\sedna").
   2) Add the bin subdirectory of sedna installation to the environment 
      variable PATH (for example "c:\sedna\bin").

Linux/Mac OS/FreeBSD/Solaris platforms:

   Sedna is distributed as a single self-extracting script.
   The installation process consists of running self-extracting script
   and following its instruction.
   Note: To avoid incompatibility problems with different glibc versions
   we recommend you building Sedna from source code.

   NOTE! The operating system user that is going to run Sedna must have 
         r-w-x permissions for the following Sedna directories:

$SEDNA_INSTALL/data
$SEDNA_INSTALL/cfg

   To grant the necessary permisions to the user on Linux/FreeBSD/Mac OS
   you can use the following command (suppose, <sedna-user> is the user 
   that is going to run Sedna):

chown <sedna-user> cfg data

   NOTE! Under FreeBSD you need also some additional steps to be done.
         See INSTALL::Post-Installation Setup::FreeBSD for the details.

   _______________________________________________________________________

                       Sedna Quick Start

   Sedna is distributed with examples and instructions on how to run them. 
   See Sedna Quick Start to start working with Sedna. Sedna Programmer's 
   Guide contains instructions on how to run example applications using 
   Sedna API. Sedna Quick Start and Sedna Programmer's Guide are available 
   at "doc" subdirectory of the directory where Sedna is installed.


